 reluctant capitulation by ukrainian president victor yanukovych ambassador pifer's article in full is available on the brookings institute website steven pifer's career as a foreign service officer centered around europe the former soviet union and arms control in addition to kyiv he has had postings in london moscow geneva and warsaw as well as on the national security council ambassador pifer is currently a visiting fellow at the brookings institution focusing on ukraine and russia issues he is a frequent invited expert speaker at the europe center html+ read more brookings institute website http www brookings edu opinions 2 search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest former us ambassador to japan discusses the okinawa base issue shorenstein aparc japan studies program in the news asahi shimbun on december 12 2011 ambassador pascual discusses common challenges facing mexico united states october 15 2010 announcement ambassador john roos visits hiroshima shorenstein aparc ksp in the news japan today on august 11 2010 paper on new start treaty by steven pifer july 29 2010 fsi stanford the europe center news erik jensen warns philippines massacre conviction could still result in impunity cddrl fsi stanford in the news the epoch times on november 25 2009 for q&a article baker offers insights on health policy issues in the 04 election october 29 2004 chp pcor news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
